Media24 has appointed Pieter du Toit as editor-in-chief of HuffPost South Africa. Du Toit was deputy editor of HuffPost South Africa since its launch in October 2016. He takes over on 1 July 2017. Du Toit has 14 years’ experience as a writer, journalist, and editor, and has worked on many of Media24’s biggest news brands, said the company. “It’s a privilege to work at a company that still believes and invests in the mission of journalism,” said Du Toit.